         <abstract>
            <p>New non-reflecting boundary conditions are introduced for the solution of the Helmholtz equation in a waveguide. These boundary conditions are perfectly transparent for all propagating modes. They do not require the determination of these propagating modes but only their propagation constants. A quasi-local form of these boundary conditions is well suited as terminating boundary condition beyond finite element meshes. Related convergence properties to the exact solution and optimal error estimates are established.</p>
          </abstract>
